snippet.textDisplay:
As a man of Korean heritage, I'm rooting for this Korean brand to do well.
But.... they need to rethink the GV80 because if they want to compete in this market, it needs a big V8 (turbocharged), at least 500 hp, beefy brakes, fat sticky tires, and cost a bit more.
At 60-70K, and not sport oriented, who is this vehicle for exactly?
People with the means to purchase a luxury SUV will do so, and gladly pay 80K+
But we want performance.
